{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d3346ed-a06d-40e4-94b1-b352c1652669","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMSTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXUnitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNUnitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTUnitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason message visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1bf28d94-d1d4-419e-af3d-fb61b0de2877","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"5C36:13E575:1C148C:2286FB:69F54ECC"},"id":"0314e45a-a600-4e8a-b3c7-5bfa542e99ef","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:09:40.460Z","parentId":"1d907a3c-cd1f-42e6-9722-ac4462ec308a"}
